title> Big Belated Thanks!</span><hr size=1> Well this is a couple days late... but work has been crazy this week. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I would like to shout a big thanks out to Morkenlar, Ajahn, Treston, Tearloch, Kiglan and Jaharad!  Because of these 6 people I am now 2 mobs away from my epic.  They helped me down the evil High Scale Kirn in the Hole on Monday night - a step I had been stuck on for a LONG time.<br>
<br>
/cheer<br>
<br>
Warning -the following is a long story recounting the evenings events.<br>
<br>
The Hole step for the shaman epic is where we all get stuck.  I have been on several raids that either didn't make it all the way to Kirn, or there was another shammy who was in line for him.  Ever since I heard that Matrex got to Kirn with just one group I thought that this would be a very fun way to do it... well this past Monday night we set it up.<br>
<br>
Mork, Treston, Ajahn, Tearloch, Kiglan and I started our personal raid on the Hole.  An exp group had just cleared down past the pool room so we were able to motor pretty quickly down to this point.  The next 100 yards is the toughest part to get through in the Hole.  We ended up with 3 or 4 Rock Golems and a couple earth pet wannabees banging on us (of course a couple un-mezzable).  We had a couple deaths but prevailed and rested up near the EXP group that had set up camp in the area.<br>
<br>
The next half hour was insane.  We tried to fight through the Rock Golem area again (got further this time) and ended up getting stuck in a spawn loop.  Ajahn had 3 to 5 mobs mezzed for about a half hour of straight battle.  Thank goodness she can steal their mana. =)  Every time we killed a couple mobs another would spawn behind us and join in the fun. We kept moving a few steps between fights and finally got to the tunnel (where things get a lot easier).  I don't think I have ever been in a fight that lasted that long - it was 30 to 45 minutes easy.  A couple times during it I thought we were going to get roasted.<br>
<br>
I was in a pretty good mood at this point because getting to Kirn from here is a piece of cake compared to what we just went though.  We cruised through the tunnel (going past Jael the Ranger Mob) and got ourselves in view of the castle/tower that Kirn calls his home.  Tearloch checks tracking... no Kirn!!  His pet is on track - but not him.  Memories of our raid for Matrex where Kirn was bugged and didn't spawn in over 8 hours (he is a 4 hour spawn) came back to me.  After all that we had gone through - was I denied again?<br>
<br>
We hoped it was a tracking bug and decided to continue on.  Ajahn told us that the the tower area was all undead mobs that don't see through ITU - and that because of the number of mobs and some really fast spawn times in the courtyard area (5 minutes!!) that ITU'ing is the best way to get to Kirn.<br>
<br>
We ITU'd up and cruised in... ITU fails and Treston, Mork and Kiglan all die!  Ajahn, Tearloch and I make it up to Kirn's area and he is up!  I am standing in front of the scaley bastard but have no way to kill him!  No melee, no way to rez the dead -just a Chanter, Druid and Shammy not sure what to do next.  We put ourselves in a nice little non-agro corner and kept ITU up while figuring out what to do. Could we charm a mob and use it against Kirn?  Some mobs are resistant to charm/mez in the Hole and we didn't want to try it out.<br>
<br>
If we just had one melee based character with us we could at least try to take Kirn out.  After a little discussion I am thinking we are done... and I am about ready to gate out.  Then some crazy monk named Jaharad claims that he can FD himself all the way down to Kirn and join us. At first I don't think this is possible. And if it is - can a monk with one druid and one shammy healing him take out Kirn?  I am doubtful, but I have hope again.<br>
<br>
A lot sooner than I expected, Jaharad runs into the room we have been hiding in and FD's on the floor.  We buff up and clear away some of the mobs between us and Kirn (about half of the mobs are non agro).  I get ready to do the hand-in and we discuss strategy.  The key thing is that I can not die during the fight - because I have to be able to loot Kirn and we have no one to rez me.<br>
<br>
I do the hand-in, Kirn takes exception and Jaharad starts wailing on him. After 30 seconds or so things are looking ok.  Jaharad is holding his own and Kirn's hps are moving.  At around 70% Ajahn lands a slow and I feel confident that we are going to succeed. Tearloch and I still have tons of mana and Kirn is down to 50% after a couple minutes.<br>
<br>
Then the last little snag in my story takes place - we can't land a snare. What will happen with Kirn decides to run?  Will he cause a train?  I test a root out, it sticks for a little bit.  At around 5% Kirn figures he has had enough and starts to walk off - luckily directly into a wall.  We try to snare and root but everything is getting resisted. How long will he run into this wall before he warps somewhere?!<br>
<br>
Finally, I land a root and nail his leezard feet to the floor.  He dies! I loot! We evac! I am overjoyed! /pant<br>
<br>
A very big thanks to everyone!  I went through a rollercoaster of emotion that night - several times thinking that Kirn would escape me once again.  Getting my epic will be anti-climatic after this little adventure. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
